This paper discusses the development of an evaluation process for automated vehicles, which involves the use of advanced technology and algorithms. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for reliable and safe testing procedures, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also touches upon the human factors involved in testing automated vehicles, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
